		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message31053865">Berserk frustrates me because even though the Golden Age is fantastic everything else afterwards is somewhat weak. Guts becomes little more than Miura's ultimate power fantasy, the side characters apart from Serpico and Isidro aren't all that interesting, Puck will forever remain unfunny 'comic relief' and the list of Berserk's faults go on. Honestly, everything that once interested me about Berserk is no longer there, especially now that the setting has become little more than a standard JRPG with elemental powers for the characters. Ultimately, I think that once Miura stopped focusing on the core element that made Berserk so interesting to begin with (the relationship between Guts and Griffith), the heart of the series was lost and it's never gotten back to the standard that the Golden Age set.<br />
<br />
The art is still fantastic, and I will admit I am curious to see <span style="text-decoration:line-through;">when<!--strike--></span> how the story ends, but I think it's unlikely that Berserk will ever really reach the heights that the Golden Age set ever again.</div><div class="postActions"></div></td>
		</tr></table></div><div class="forum_boardrowspacer">&nbsp;</div>
