		  <td width="135" class="forum_boardrow2" style="border-width: 0px 0px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="messageuser32165301" style="padding-bottom: 2px;"><a href="/profile/Po_and_Dong"><strong>Po_and_Dong</strong></a></div>
		  
		  <a href="/profile/Po_and_Dong"><img src="http://cdn.myanimelist.net/images/useravatars/3599051.jpg" vspace="2" border="0"></a>
		  <br>
		  Offline<br>
		  Joined: Feb 2014<br>
		  Posts: 22
		  </td>
		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message32165301">Golden Age by far the best arc, has the same well drawn action the series is famous for, keeps the aesthetic that has become iconic, and has a great story, perfectly paced and ends with an absurd and memorable climax. One of my favorite parts in any manga.<br />
<br />
I also think people overblow the quality decrease after Golden Age tremendously. Some would have it in their heads that everything after Golden Age is loli witch shenanigans when there is an entire two arcs between Golden Age and that. Berserk was clearly planned to go into the magic department from the beginning, and so things increasingly progressed into the weird. People may not like it, but I'm hard pressed to call it random when there are elves and demon lords in the first few volumes.<br />
<br />
The character of Griffith largely disappearrs from the reader's radar after Golden Age, readers can no longer see his personality and development like they could in Golden Age. But of course you can't, thats the symbolism of the Eclipse, he loses his humanity. Here's a down to earth statement if you think I'm grasping for straws, a character like Griffith can't stay villainous and frightening if you can see right into your head. Going beyond this Golden Age largely resolved Griffith's character arc. Do we really need to see more Griffith, as a character rather than a plot device. Not now, the Band of the Hawk is over, now its Gut's adventure.<br />
<br />
Fittingly so, most of the character development goes to Gut's slow mental breakdown that progresses up until he gets some travellers, his attempt to rape Casca and his increasing violent insanity represented by the hellhound. Random character development to show how mean he is in battle? NO, trauma from the Eclipse. Guts is a great character that simply goes through SO much shit and is so hardened most of the time that the few instances we see his vulnerability after Golden Age have more impact.<br />
<br />
I liked the Tower of Retribution arc alot, it had a clear plot development in mind (the birth of Griffith so he can start the age of darkness) had some little mystery about the Behelit Apostle, and had much more twisted and dark sequences in lieu of the Eclipse. By far the darkest arc in the entire manga, and my favorite besides Golden Age because it is a good progression from the realism of Golden Age into the more dark and crazy world Berserk was introduced as (Black Swordsman). And as I said before all of the action in Berserk is well above average.<br />
<br />
The witch/troll arc is when people start to complain. It introduces more high fantasy types of magic instead of the grimdark demon stuff that was put into the series before. Reception is mixed. I don't think anyone claims its one of the best arcs but at the same time is it really that bad? To put it simply we can examine it piece by piece, comparing it with the supposedly superior Golden Age.<br />
<br />
Crazy and awesome action Berserk is famous for:: CHECK<br />
-people dont like the Berserker armor, it makes the series to &quot;shoneny&quot;, I think those people should reexamine what shonen means before they apply it to something like Berserk.<br />
<br />
Good character stuff:: NOPE<br />
-You don't see any of the subtle deprecation of Gut's personality as so in Tower of Retribution, or someone else thats interesting like Griffith. You may see some interesting characters like the old witch, but they aren't anything overly memorable. Does it make the arc shit? Hardly.<br />
<br />
Aesthetic appeal:: CHECK<br />
-Berserk didn't lose its famous grimdark bloody -berserk- rage stuff it has always has in this arc. They introduced some magic weapons, Guts also went into the cesspool of a demon tree. People should stop overblowing this.<br />
<br />
STORY:: CHECK(?)<br />
-Was this a bad story? Not in my opinion. Read real shitty manga and learn what a real bad story is before you call this terrible, please. Its such a subjective area though, I would rather just address individual qualms if someone responds to me with their opinion. The story kept me glued to the screen same as any other arc. Less so? Yes. Alot less so? No.<br />
Also people complain about how Falconia came out of nowhere and didn't make sense. What didn't make sense exactly, between the demon kings and the giant flying skull man? More specifically, Falconia wasn't foreshadowed, I can agree. Some Foreshadowing never hurts.<br />
<br />
Is Berserk too long? No, I don't think so. It's an epic manga, epic as a noun here. I like the story grandoise and long, in retrospect I want to see it as a huge adventure. One big plot development per arc is the formula so far, just like an epic. Golden Age had the eclipse, Tower of Retribution the birth of Griffith, Millenium Falcon arc had the creation of Falconia. This current arc will likely conclude with the arrival at Elfheim.<br />
<br />
Is Berserk too slow? Yes. That has nothing to do with the manga itself though, the canon is irrespective of Miura's gaming habits.<br />
<br />
Is Berserk overrated/underrated? There is probably 1 hipster for every 5 superfans, and honestly I don't give a shit. Let me put it this way, if you find yourself asking this question then abort right there, you are on the wrong path of thought.<br />
<br />
Berserk is one of my favorite manga, but I don't have a bias towards it. I understand that some people geniuely don't like it. I also understand that the rise of verbose and dramatic criticisms in proportion to its popularity is likely not a coincidence.</div><div class="postActions"></div></td>
		</tr></table></div><div class="forum_boardrowspacer">&nbsp;</div>
