		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message32195021">I think the problem isn't so much that people think the post-Golden Age arcs are &quot;terribad&quot;, but that it's disappointing to go from &quot;Incredible&quot; and &quot;Nigh-Perfection&quot; to &quot;Pretty decent, I guess,&quot; type of quality. I'd even argue the fairie arc was pretty poor and drawn out. The pacing was bad and there were dozens of panels of just fairies being slashed. <br />
<br />
That said, Berserk is good. It is an epic, like you describe, and you're right in everything you said. If it were being released faster, the complaints would be completely different. But people wait on bated breath for Golden Age level of quality, and wait a long time, at that, to receive, I don't know, 6/10 quality of work? I hate to throw out a number, but I can't think of an anime to compare it to off the top of my head. <br />
<br />
Point is, a common flaw amongst masterpieces is that you can't compare to your own works. It happens all the time. Miura has blatantly hit that wall, and the fanbase cringes seeing Miura stumped. At least, I know I do.</div><div class="postActions"></div><div class="sig"><span style="font-size: 80%;"><div style="text-align: center;"><img class="userimg" data-src="http://fc06.deviantart.net/fs42/f/2009/096/7/8/Tonberry_Banner_by_Doaj.jpg" /><br />
